FBIS4-66919 "jptac005__l94034" JPRS-TAC-94-005-L JPRS Arms Control 7 May 1994 CENTRAL EURASIA UKRAINE Shmarov, U.S. Envoy Discuss Nuclear Weapons, Conversion Shmarov, U.S. Envoy Discuss Nuclear Weapons, Conversion PM0905092994 Moscow TRUD in Russian 7 May 94 p 3 PM0905092994 Moscow TRUD Russian BFN [Report from roundup of UKRINFORM and TASS reports: "Defense Industry Open to Businessmen"] [Text] An exchange of opinions on the fulfillment of the agreements reached in Moscow between the Ukrainian, U.S., and Russian presidents on the elimination of the nuclear weapons on Ukrainian soil took place between Ukrainian Vice Premier Valeriy Shmarov and Nicholas Burns, head of the U.S. economic delegation and senior director of the National Security Council. The guest was also familiarized with the programs for the conversion of Ukraine's defense industry which propose close cooperation with U.S. firms. Conversion processes could be considerably accelerated by the involvement of small-scale business as the most mobile form of entrepreneurship. The U.S. side's attention was drawn also to problems of Ukraine's space complex, where there is extensive scope for cooperation.
